  "prompt": "Why is M&M's motto \"melts in your mouth, not in your hand\"?",
  "response": "M&M's motto \"melts in your mouth, not in your hand\" was introduced to emphasize the candy's hard sugar shell, which prevents the chocolate inside from melting too quickly when held. This feature was particularly appealing to consumers who wanted a chocolate treat that wouldn't get messy or melt easily in their hands. The slogan successfully communicated a unique selling point of M&M's and contributed to its branding and market appeal.",
